Yeah!

246
00:16:56,600 --> 00:16:57,200
Ahh!

247
00:16:58,900 --> 00:17:02,600
I'm not using this for weird 
things... don't worry!

248
00:17:03,200 --> 00:17:04,700
They're all weird posters.

249
00:17:05,600 --> 00:17:08,900
What do you mean? They're 
all superstars of the era!

250
00:17:09,300 --> 00:17:18,200
Taking a small possible situation, tying it 
to a sure chance, and grabbing the glory.
They all made my dreams come true!




251
00:17:20,300 --> 00:17:22,500
And one day, you, too, will...

252
00:17:23,400 --> 00:17:24,800
No, not me.

253
00:17:35,300 --> 00:17:38,800
What is she doing out still?

254
00:17:39,800 --> 00:17:41,300
Uhm, hello...

255
00:17:41,300 --> 00:17:48,100
Pin pon pan pon! This number is no
longer in service, so... excuse me!

256
00:17:48,300 --> 00:17:50,200
Ahh, you're Jigoro-san, correct?

257
00:17:50,500 --> 00:17:53,000
I'm fine, thank you. Excuse me!

258
00:17:53,200 --> 00:17:55,200
W... wait, Jigoro-sama!

259
00:17:55,400 --> 00:17:56,000
Excuse me!

260
00:17:56,000 --> 00:17:57,200
Jigoro-sensei!

261
00:17:57,500 --> 00:17:58,200
Yes, what?

262
00:18:02,800 --> 00:18:06,000
No way, this my room?

263
00:18:06,500 --> 00:18:09,500
Okay, next is dinner prep.

264
00:18:09,800 --> 00:18:13,300
Ah, it's okay, there's a good ramen 
shop just around the corner.

265
00:18:13,800 --> 00:18:16,300
You probably eat ramen all time, right?

266
00:18:16,500 --> 00:18:16,900
Eh?


267
00:18:17,400 --> 00:18:18,800
Are there any grocery shops nearby?

268
00:18:19,100 --> 00:18:21,300
Yeah, there's a convenience store...

269
00:18:21,440 --> 00:18:23,400
I'll make you beef stroganoff.

270
00:18:23,900 --> 00:18:27,200
B... beef stroga.. what's that?

271
00:18:27,600 --> 00:18:28,600
A thank you gift for today.

272
00:18:32,900 --> 00:18:35,300
Hey, what's this car? Don't push, man!

273
00:18:35,300 --> 00:18:36,200
Which newspaper company is it?

274
00:18:36,300 --> 00:18:37,900
Stupid, it can't be a newspaper company!


275
00:18:43,100 --> 00:18:45,340
News reporters, great job, great job.

276
00:18:45,700 --> 00:18:47,300
I am here to escort you.

277
00:18:48,000 --> 00:18:49,600
Inokuma-san, where are you going?

278
00:18:51,100 --> 00:18:55,400
I've been invited to dinner. What 
was it that's being served?

279
00:18:55,800 --> 00:18:58,500
A bit of French cuisine, sire.

280
00:18:58,500 --> 00:19:01,700
A bit, a bit! I'm eating that.

281
00:19:03,900 --> 00:19:09,700
Delicious! This is really delicious! We should've called your grandfather over!


282
00:19:11,800 --> 00:19:16,100
What's wrong, aren't you gonna eat? If 
you don't eat, you won't become strong!

283
00:19:17,200 --> 00:19:19,900
I don't care about getting strong.

284
00:19:21,750 --> 00:19:23,900
When did you start doing judo?

285
00:19:24,600 --> 00:19:25,700
I don't know...

286
00:19:28,600 --> 00:19:34,900
But, I do remember stomach throwing
my father when I was 5 years old.

287
00:19:34,900 --> 00:19:35,430
5 years old?!

288
00:19:36,300 --> 00:19:39,500
I wanted to be praised by everyone.

289
00:19:40,600 --> 00:19:48,900
Of course, grandpa was overjoyed, but at 
that time, it seemed like my mother was 
in the shadows of the dojo, crying.

290
00:19:49,800 --> 00:19:53,800
At that time, I had no idea that 
I was different than other kids.

291
00:19:54,600 --> 00:19:56,400
But, my mother must have known.

292
00:19:57,500 --> 00:20:00,800
When I got in junior high, I finally noticed it.


293
00:20:01,400 --> 00:20:06,600
All my friends weren't doing 
morning and night practices.

294
00:20:08,700 --> 00:20:16,100
Everyone wore pretty clothes, 
and dated boys, having fun...

295
00:20:16,900 --> 00:20:19,100
While only I... only I...

296
00:20:23,600 --> 00:20:31,400
I don't hate judo. But, I just want to 
be a normal girl... just a normal girl.

297
00:20:36,600 --> 00:20:44,100
I... I don't know how many times I cried...
for exactly the opposite reason.

298
00:20:45,100 --> 00:20:49,200
I told you before, right, that my 
dream was a sports star.

299
00:20:49,900 --> 00:20:55,900
A sports star that gave everyone a chance
to dream... that's what I wanted to be.

300
00:20:58,800 --> 00:21:07,200
Baseball, soccer, rugby... I did all 
kinds, but none of them clicked.

301
00:21:07,700 --> 00:21:14,900
In the end, I always cried... it was rough, you know, to give up each dream, one by one.

302
00:21:21,000 --> 00:21:24,200
Ah, heck! All of that is history!

303
00:21:24,800 --> 00:21:30,100
I'm pretty satisfied now, with being a newspaper reporter. People are strange, huh?

304
00:21:34,200 --> 00:21:35,000
This is delicious!



305
00:21:44,000 --> 00:21:45,600
Ahh, I'll clean it up!

306
00:21:46,400 --> 00:21:48,600
Don't worry. I'm used to it.

307
00:21:49,200 --> 00:21:51,100
Really, you can just leave it there...

308
00:21:51,100 --> 00:21:51,700
Eeek!

309
00:21:51,800 --> 00:21:52,200
What?

310
00:21:53,500 --> 00:21:54,700
A c... cockroach just...

311
00:21:55,200 --> 00:21:58,700
Eeek... ran.. it ran...

312
00:21:58,800 --> 00:22:02,600
A cockroach ran! Gross!

313
00:22:03,000 --> 00:22:05,100
She really is just a normal girl.

314
00:22:05,200 --> 00:22:08,500
What are you doing? Please 
hurry up and catch it!

315
00:22:08,700 --> 00:22:10,200
What, me?

316
00:22:10,700 --> 00:22:14,900
Ah, don't tell me that you're afraid of cockroaches, too, Matsuda-san!

317
00:22:15,800 --> 00:22:19,100
Wha... no way, it's just a cockroach...

318
00:22:21,800 --> 00:22:23,000
Dohhyah!

319
00:22:23,800 --> 00:22:26,400
The cockroach flew!

320
00:22:27,200 --> 00:22:28,000
Another plateful!

321
00:22:28,400 --> 00:22:31,000
U... uhm... Inokuma-sensei.

322
00:22:31,000 --> 00:22:31,500
Hm?

323
00:22:32,650 --> 00:22:35,600
Isn't it time to discuss being 
Sayaka's coach...

324
00:22:36,600 --> 00:22:38,100
Don't sweat it.

325
00:22:38,270 --> 00:22:38,900
Hah...

326
00:22:39,400 --> 00:22:40,100
But...

327
00:22:40,200 --> 00:22:44,030
But this food is really delicious. 
Another plateful, jya!

328
00:22:45,000 --> 00:22:47,200
The fifth helping... right?

329
00:22:47,300 --> 00:22:49,800
What a grand person!

330
00:22:50,400 --> 00:22:53,600
The boldness of requesting seconds 
at a prestigious restaurant!

331
00:22:53,700 --> 00:22:59,200
This is a challenge to the weight-classes
and rules and manners of the 
Japanese Judo Federation!

332
00:23:05,600 --> 00:23:11,900
He can do it! The master will definitely bring about a revolution in the Japanese judo world!

333
00:23:13,400 --> 00:23:14,300
Another plateful, please!

334
00:23:17,200 --> 00:23:23,800
971 days until Barcelona Olympics

335
00:23:27,900 --> 00:23:31,300
Hey, Grandpa, are you really going
to be Sayaka-san's coach?

336
00:23:32,600 --> 00:23:36,500
This is tasty, too. Yawara, I 
want more kimpira goboh!

337
00:23:36,600 --> 00:23:40,800
Geez... Grandpa, I'm going to be in a match.

338
00:23:41,000 --> 00:23:43,400
W... what did you say?

339
00:23:43,750 --> 00:23:48,600
Next time, on "Yawara"... Enough of 
Judo! I'm going to be in a match!

340
00:23:49,100 --> 00:23:52,300
If you don't watch it, I'll do a 
yoko shihoh gatame on you!
